arXiv:2404.13029v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We introduce a non-commutative product for curved spacetimes, that can be regarded as a generalization of the Rieffel (or Moyal-Weyl) product. This product employs the exponential map and a Poisson tensor, and the deformed product maintains associativity under the condition that the Poisson tensor $\Theta$ satisfies $\Theta^{\mu
u}
abla_{
u}\Theta^{ho\sigma}=0$, in relation to a Levi-Cevita connection. We proceed to solve the associativity condition for various physical spacetimes, uncovering non-commutative structures with compelling properties.
